(secondQuint)A Study to Evaluate the Effectiveness and Safety of Paliperidone Palmitate in Subjects With Acute Schizophrenia.

 This is an open-label (all people know the identity of the intervention), prospective (looking forward using periodic observations collected predominantly following participant enrollment), non-comparative and multicenter study to evaluate the effectiveness and safety of paliperidone palmitate in acute schizophrenic participants.

 This study consists of a screening phase (up to 7 days), treatment phase (13 weeks), and a study completion or early withdrawal visit.

 Safety evaluations will include adverse events, clinical laboratory tests, concomitant medications, physical examination, and vital signs, which will be monitored throughout the study.

 The total duration of study participation for each participant will be approximately 13 weeks.

